                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work ፍትሃ፡ ነገስት is crudely written on the front board in large felt-tip pen.&#xD;
- Seal of the parish council of Golʿa Däbrä Bǝrhan Yoḥannǝs church: fols. 4r, 116r, 232r.&#xD;
- Crude note written in pen in the upper margin: fol. 81v.&#xD;
- Corrections over erasures on many fols., carefully executed in the main hand: e.g., fols. 8v, 9r, 14ra, 14v, 15r etc.&#xD;
- Corrected passages are written over erasures interlineally, in somewhat smaller script, in the same hand, on many fols.: e.g., fols. 11ra, 13va, 18va, 38ra etc.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with thin black and red lines, on many fols.: e.g., fols. 12va-vb, 13va, 20ra, 24vb etc.&#xD;
- Omitted letter or word added interlineally: fol. 14vb.&#xD;
- Omitted passage added in the upper margin (?): fol. 32r.&#xD;
- A sign in the shape of cross (possibly tämälläs-sign, but no omitted text passages are indicated in the margin), poorly visible, on many fols.: e.g., fols. 31v, 34v, 36r, 40r, 45r, 49v etc.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign in the shapf of two perpendicular lines, indicating where the omitted word or letters, written in the margin in a secondary hand, belong: fols. 41v, 43r(?), 47v, 50r, 52r, 53r.&#xD;
- A passage of the text is taken in a red frame: fol. 45v.</item>
